Name
       gui_clear_highlight_safety_mechanism  -  Clears  the  highlights on the
       specified type of safety mechanisms

Syntax
       gui_clear_highlight_safety_mechanism

       [-help]

       {[-dcls  | -tmr  | -ser ]}

       Clears the highlights on the specified type of safety  mechanisms.  You
       must specify at least one type of safety mechanism.

       The gui_clear_highlight_safety_mechanism command can be used only after
       a  USF  file  has been loaded. If this command is run before the safety
       flow is enabled, the tool gives the following error:

       **ERROR: (IMPGUI-3009): The safety flow is not enabled

Parameters
       -help  Prints   a   brief   description    of    the    gui_clear_high-
              light_safety_mechanism command.

              For  a detailed description of the command, use the man command:
              man gui_clear_highlight_safety_mechanism.

       -dcls  Removes the highlights from all instances and all internal,  in-
              terface,  common,  and  top  nets  of Dual Core Lock Step (DCLS)
              groups.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -ser   Removes the highlights from all Soft Error Resilience (SER)  in-
              stances.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -tmr   Removes  the highlights from all Triple Modular Redundancy (TMR)
              parents, clones, and voters.

              Data_type: bool, required

Example
              * The following command removes highlights from all TMR parents,
                clones, and voters:

                gui_clear_highlight_safety_mechanism -tmr

